title: Looking back and ahead at BYU's football schedule following win over Cincinnati
text:
Looking back and ahead at BYU's football schedule following win over Cincinnati
Upcoming Games BYU Football BYU Wagner @ BYU Lavell Edwards Stadium, Provo Oct. 24, 1:00 p.m. 5 Days 18 Hrs 57 Mins 51 Secs More Coverage BYU, winners of 3 in a row, enters into softest part of its schedule BYU defeated Cincinnati 38-24 on Friday. Here's a look of how each team on BYU's schedule performed over the weekend:
NEBRASKA (3-4): Beat Minnesota 48-25. Up next: Saturday vs. Northwestern (5-2).
BOISE STATE (5-2): Lost to Utah State, 52-26. Up next: Saturday vs. Wyoming (1-6).
UCLA (4-2): Lost to Stanford, 56-35. Up next: Thursday vs. California (5-1).
MICHIGAN (5-2): Lost to Michigan State, 27-23. Up next: Bye.
CONNECTICUT (3-4): Lost to South Florida, 28-20. Up next: Saturday at Cincinnati (3-3).
EAST CAROLINA (4-3): Beat Tulsa, 30-17. Up next: Thursday vs. Temple (6-0).
CINCINNATI (3-3): Lost to BYU, 38-24. Up next: Saturday vs. Connecticut (3-4).
WAGNER (0-6): Lost to Saint Francis, 43-14. Up next: Saturday vs. BYU (5-2).
SAN JOSE STATE (3-4): Lost to San Diego State, 30-7. Up next: Saturday vs. New Mexico (4-3).
MISSOURI (4-3): Lost to Georgia, 9-6. Up next: Saturday at Vanderbilt (2-4).
FRESNO STATE (2-5): Beat UNLV , 31-28. Up next: Saturday at Air Force (3-3).
UTAH STATE (4-2): Beat Boise State, 52-26. Up next: Friday at San Diego State (4-3).
